# 1ï¸âƒ£ Real-Time Operating System (RTOS)

---

## ğŸ”¹ What Does â€œReal-Timeâ€ Mean?

### â±ï¸ Key Idea

> **Correctness depends on time**, not only on output.

### ğŸ§  Two Execution Worlds

| Mode              | Meaning                         |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------- |
| **Nonâ€“Real-Time** | Output matters, time doesnâ€™t    |
| **Real-Time**     | Output + strict time constraint |

---

### ğŸ¥ Real-Life Analogy (YouTube Example)

* **Recorded Video** â†’ Non-real-time

  * You can watch **anytime**
* **YouTube Live** â†’ Real-time

  * Speaker talks ğŸ—£ï¸
  * Listener hears **immediately**

ğŸ“Œ **Delay = unacceptable (or partially acceptable)**

---

## ğŸ”¹ Types of Real-Time OS

![Image](https://users.ece.cmu.edu/~koopman/des_s99/real_time/rts1_fig1.gif)

