### ğŸŸ¥ Hard Real-Time OS

> **Deadline miss = system failure âŒ**

#### ğŸ”¥ Characteristics

* Extremely strict timing
* No delay tolerated
* Life / mission critical

#### ğŸš€ Examples

* Missile guidance systems
* Flight control systems
* Medical life-support machines

ğŸ“Œ If task is supposed to execute at **5 seconds**,
â¡ï¸ **5.0001 sec = failure**

---

### ğŸŸ¨ Soft Real-Time OS

> **Delay acceptable, but performance degrades**

#### ğŸ® Examples

* Online gaming
* Video streaming
* YouTube Live
* Multimedia systems

ğŸ“Œ 5â€“10 sec delay â‰  disaster
ğŸ“Œ But user experience reduces

---

## ğŸ”‘ RTOS Summary Table

| Feature         | Hard RTOS       | Soft RTOS         |
| --------------- | --------------- | ----------------- |
| Deadline        | Absolute        | Flexible          |
| Delay Tolerance | âŒ None          | âœ… Small           |
| Failure Impact  | Catastrophic    | Acceptable        |
| Examples        | Missile, Flight | Gaming, Streaming |

