# 2ï¸âƒ£ Distributed Operating System

---

## ğŸ”¹ Core Idea

> **Multiple independent systems**, connected by a network,
> working together **geographically distributed**.

---

### ğŸŒ Architecture Explanation

![Image](https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20240429162227/Distributed-Operating-System_1.webp)

![Image](https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20240806125841/Client-Server-Architecture-in-Distributed-Systems.webp)

```
System A (Kernel + RAM + Disk)
        â”‚
System B (Kernel + RAM + Disk)
        â”‚
System C (Kernel + RAM + Disk)
        â”‚
     Network
```

ğŸ“Œ **Loosely Coupled Systems**

* Own memory
* Own CPU
* Own OS kernel
* Independent failure possible

---

### ğŸŒ Real-World Examples

* Google services
* Facebook data centers
* Global databases

ğŸ“Œ Data & computation are **not kept at one place**

---

## ğŸ”¹ Advantages of Distributed OS

| Benefit         | Meaning                                |
| --------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Availability    | System stays up even if one node fails |
| Fault Tolerance | Failure handled gracefully             |
| Scalability     | Add more machines easily               |
| Load Balancing  | Work distributed evenly                |

---

# 3ï¸âƒ£ Clustered Operating System

---

## ğŸ”¹ Core Idea

> **Multiple machines connected in a local network**,
> working together like **ONE powerful machine**.

---

### ğŸ§© Architecture Visualization

![Image](https://scaler.com/topics/images/representation-of-clustered-operating-system.webp)

