```

ğŸ“Œ **Tightly Coupled**

* Same location
* Same LAN
* Controlled together

---

### âš¡ Why Clusters Are Used?

* High computation power
* Parallel processing
* High availability
* Load sharing

ğŸ“Œ 100 machines = ~100Ã— power (conceptually)

---

## ğŸ”¹ Clustered OS Advantages

| Feature           | Explanation                       |
| ----------------- | --------------------------------- |
| High Availability | One node fails â†’ others take over |
| Fault Tolerance   | No single point of failure        |
| Scalability       | Add nodes easily                  |
| Performance       | Increased throughput              |

---

## ğŸ†š Distributed vs Clustered OS (Very Important)

| Feature  | Distributed OS           | Clustered OS               |
| -------- | ------------------------ | -------------------------- |
| Location | Geographically separated | Same location              |
| Coupling | Loosely coupled          | Tightly coupled            |
| Network  | WAN / Internet           | LAN                        |
| View     | Independent systems      | Single system image        |
| Use Case | Global services          | High-performance computing |

---

# 4ï¸âƒ£ Embedded Operating System

---

## ğŸ”¹ Core Definition

> An **Embedded OS** is designed for a **specific device**
> performing a **fixed, dedicated function**.

---

### ğŸ  Everyday Examples

![Image](https://res.cloudinary.com/rs-designspark-live/image/upload/c_limit%2Cw_750/f_auto/v1/article/Embedded-System-and-Its-Real-Time-Applications-Image-31_efa1db2ec38ce29798e756d7d285968babde79a6)

