* Washing machine
* Microwave oven
* Air conditioner
* Digital camera
* Traffic light controller

ğŸ“Œ One device â†’ One purpose â†’ Fixed behavior

---

## ğŸ”’ Key Characteristics

* Limited hardware
* Fixed functionality
* No user programmability
* Highly optimized
* Reliable & efficient

âŒ You **cannot**:

* Install apps
* Change OS behavior
* Modify instructions dynamically

---

### ğŸ§  Analogy

* **Embedded system** = Calculator
* **Normal computer** = Smartphone

ğŸ“Œ Calculator wonâ€™t become a phone
ğŸ“Œ Computer can become anything (via software)

---

## ğŸ§¾ Embedded vs Non-Embedded System

| Feature       | Embedded System | General Computer |
| ------------- | --------------- | ---------------- |
| Purpose       | Fixed           | Flexible         |
| User Control  | Very limited    | Full             |
| OS Modifiable | âŒ No            | âœ… Yes            |
| Examples      | AC, Microwave   | Laptop, PC       |

---

# ğŸ”š Final Exam-Ready Summary ğŸ’

### âœ… Real-Time OS

* Output + **time constraint**
* Hard RTOS â†’ No delay
* Soft RTOS â†’ Small delay allowed

### âœ… Distributed OS

* Systems spread geographically
* Independent nodes
* High availability & scalability

### âœ… Clustered OS

* Systems in same location
* Work as one powerful system
* High performance & fault tolerance

### âœ… Embedded OS

* Fixed functionality
* Device-specific
* Highly reliable & optimized

